<h3 dir=3D"auto">Bug: Sidebar Expand/Collapse Icons Display Incorrectly</=
h3>


<p dir=3D"auto">The <code class=3D"notranslate">MacOSSidebar</code> incor=
rectly uses the <code class=3D"notranslate">flatIndex</code> when checkin=
g the <code class=3D"notranslate">_expandedIndices</code> set in <code cl=
ass=3D"notranslate">_buildAwesomeSidebarItem</code> and <code class=3D"no=
translate">_buildSidebarItem</code>. Since <code class=3D"notranslate">_e=
xpandedIndices</code> stores <code class=3D"notranslate">originalIndex</c=
ode>, this mismatch causes the expand/collapse icons to display the wrong=
 state and prevents expandable items from toggling correctly.</p>


